{
  "text": "In other words, the DoF of a full SO(3) is three. Note that a rotational matrix can alternatively be represented by the Euler angles decomposition [CITATION_1] . A bijective mapping ∨ : so(3) → R 3 and its reverse mapping ∧ : R 3 → so(3) are defined asω ∨ = ω, and ω ∧ =ω, respectively. Let ν ∈ R 3 , an element of se(3) can then be identified aŝ",
